### UniversalAdapters/converters/batch-converter.js

**Purpose:** Node.js batch converter that reads all SKILL.md files from a source directory and converts them to all supported adapter platforms in one pass. Uses the adapter plugin system from `UniversalAdapters/adapters/`.

**Status:** Active -- standalone utility, independent from the Python pipeline.

#### Usage

```bash
node UniversalAdapters/converters/batch-converter.js <source-dir> <output-dir>
```

#### Arguments

| Position | Default | Description |
|---|---|---|
| 1 (`source-dir`) | `.` | Directory to scan recursively for SKILL.md files |
| 2 (`output-dir`) | `./output` | Root output directory; each platform gets a subdirectory |

No named flags. Arguments are positional.

#### Input / Output

| Direction | Path | Format |
|---|---|---|
| Input | `<source-dir>/**/**/SKILL.md` | YAML frontmatter + Markdown (recursive scan) |
| Output | `<output-dir>/<platform>/<slug>/` | Platform-specific files as determined by each adapter |

Supported platforms are determined dynamically by `adapters.listPlatforms()`. The adapters directory contains 8 adapter modules: claude-cli, claude-desktop, claude-web, codex-cli, copilot-cli, gemini-cli, github-repo, and index.

#### Examples

```bash
# Convert all master skills to all adapter platforms
node UniversalAdapters/converters/batch-converter.js _master-skills ./UniversalAdapters/output

# Convert a subset directory
node UniversalAdapters/converters/batch-converter.js _master-skills/technical ./output-technical
```

#### Notes

- Handles cross-category slug collisions by prepending `{category}--` when duplicate slugs are detected across categories.
- Parses the full SKILL.md body and maps master sections (Overview, When to Use, Core Processes, etc.) to adapter content fields.
- Prints a success/failure summary and lists the first 10 errors if any conversions fail.
- No npm install required; uses only `fs`, `path`, and the local adapters module.

