## Deprecated Scripts

The following scripts are maintained for backward compatibility but should not be used for new work. Each delegates to the active replacement when possible.

---

### convert_to_gems.py

**Purpose:** Converts SKILL.md files to Gemini Gem JSON format.

**Status:** Deprecated. Use `python sync-skills.py --targets gemini` instead.

When imported libraries are available, this script delegates to the `GeminiConverter` class from `sync-skills.py`. Otherwise, it falls back to its own inline conversion logic.

#### Arguments

| Flag | Type | Default | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| `--category` | choice | none | Process only this category (choices: technical, strategy, creative, industry, operations, ai-agents) |
| `--model-override` | string | none | Force a specific Gemini model for every gem (e.g., `gemini-2.5-pro`) |
| `--dry-run` | flag | off | Preview without writing files |

#### Legacy Usage

```bash
python convert_to_gems.py
python convert_to_gems.py --category technical
python convert_to_gems.py --category strategy --model-override gemini-2.5-pro
python convert_to_gems.py --dry-run
```

---

### convert_to_codex_responses.py

**Purpose:** Converts SKILL.md files to OpenAI Responses API format, plus GPT Builder, Agent Builder, and system-prompt TXT formats.

**Status:** Deprecated. Use `python sync-skills.py --targets codex` instead.

Delegates to the `CodexResponsesConverter` class when available. This standalone script generates 5 formats (responses, gpts, agents, system-prompts, cli/AGENTS.md) while sync-skills.py generates the core 3 (responses, gpts, system-prompts). The agent.json and cli/AGENTS.md formats are unique to this script.

#### Arguments

| Flag | Type | Default | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| `--source` | path | `_master-skills/` | Source master-skills directory |
| `--target` | path | `CodexSkills/` | Output directory |
| `--category` | string | none | Convert only this category |
| `--skill` | string | none | Convert only this skill name |
| `--dry-run` | flag | off | Preview without writing files |

#### Legacy Usage

```bash
python convert_to_codex_responses.py
python convert_to_codex_responses.py --category technical
python convert_to_codex_responses.py --skill api-development
python convert_to_codex_responses.py --dry-run
```

---

### convert_to_cli_skills.py

**Purpose:** Universal CLI skill placer that converts master skills into platform-specific CLI skill formats for Claude CLI, Gemini CLI, Codex CLI, and GitHub Copilot CLI.

**Status:** Deprecated. Use `python sync-skills.py --targets cli` instead.

#### Arguments

| Flag | Type | Default | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| `--platforms` | string | `all` | Comma-separated list: `claude`, `gemini`, `codex`, `copilot`, or `all` |
| `--category` | choice | none | Convert only skills from this category |
| `--skill` | string | none | Convert only this specific skill (by directory name) |
| `--dry-run` | flag | off | Show what would be done without writing files |

#### Legacy Usage

```bash
python convert_to_cli_skills.py --platforms all
python convert_to_cli_skills.py --platforms claude,gemini
python convert_to_cli_skills.py --platforms codex --category technical
python convert_to_cli_skills.py --platforms all --skill api-development
python convert_to_cli_skills.py --platforms all --dry-run
```

---

### convert-to-copilot.js

**Purpose:** JavaScript converter that generates GitHub Copilot-specific formats: custom-instructions, agent-skills, path-specific instructions, and category READMEs.

**Status:** Deprecated. Use `python sync-skills.py --targets copilot` instead.

This JS converter duplicates the `CopilotConverter` class in `sync-skills.py` and cannot share the Python `lib/` modules. It will be removed in a future version.

#### Usage

```bash
node convert-to-copilot.js
```

No command-line arguments. Source and target directories are hardcoded:

| Direction | Path |
|---|---|
| Input | `_master-skills/{category}/{slug}/SKILL.md` |
| Output | `GithubCopilot/CopilotSkills/custom-instructions/` |
| Output | `GithubCopilot/CopilotSkills/agent-skills/` |
| Output | `GithubCopilot/CopilotSkills/instructions/` |

---

### fix_skills.py / fix_skills_structure.py / fix_skills_pass3.py

**Purpose:** Original three-file quality fixer pipeline. Each script handles one pass of quality fixes on `_master-skills/` SKILL.md files.

**Status:** Deprecated. Use `python fix_skills_unified.py` instead.

| Script | Pass | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `fix_skills.py` | 1 | Frontmatter repair, description generation, trigger verbs |
| `fix_skills_structure.py` | 2 | Heading promotion, workflow section headings |
| `fix_skills_pass3.py` | 3 | Name slugification, description trimming |

All three scripts accept `--all`, `--dry-run`, and related flags. The unified replacement provides identical functionality with shared I/O and a single `--pass` selector.

#### Legacy Usage

```bash
# Old pipeline (deprecated)
python fix_skills.py --all
python fix_skills_structure.py --all
python fix_skills_pass3.py --all

# New equivalent
python fix_skills_unified.py --all
```

---

## Common Workflows

### Full Rebuild

Rebuilds all platform outputs from scratch. Run from the project root.

```bash
export PYTHONIOENCODING=utf-8

# Step 1: Fix all master skills
python fix_skills_unified.py --all

# Step 2: Sync to all platform outputs
python sync-skills.py --targets all --validate --stats

# Step 3: Populate bundles, variants, and cleanup
python populate_all.py --phase all
```

### Single Category Update

Update only one category (e.g., after adding new skills to `_master-skills/technical/`).

```bash
export PYTHONIOENCODING=utf-8

python fix_skills_unified.py --category technical
python sync-skills.py --targets all --category technical --stats
python populate_all.py --phase all
```

### Dry-Run Validation

Preview all changes without writing any files.

```bash
export PYTHONIOENCODING=utf-8

python fix_skills_unified.py --all --dry-run --verbose
python sync-skills.py --targets all --dry-run --validate --stats
python populate_all.py --phase all --dry-run
```

### Single Platform Sync

Regenerate output for only one platform.

```bash
# Gemini only
python sync-skills.py --targets gemini --stats

# Codex only
python sync-skills.py --targets codex --validate

# CLI variants only
python sync-skills.py --targets cli
```

### Single Skill Fix and Sync

Fix and sync a specific skill.

```bash
python fix_skills_unified.py --skill technical/api-development
python sync-skills.py --targets all --skill technical/api-development
```

### Universal Adapter Batch Convert

Run the Node.js adapter-based conversion independently of the Python pipeline.

```bash
node UniversalAdapters/converters/batch-converter.js _master-skills ./UniversalAdapters/output
```
